Complained of dizziness and light headedness. Patient approached me with sudden dizziness. LIght headed, and felt cold. After walking to treatment area, obtained vitals. Heart rate slightly elevated at 106. After sitting and talking with me for 5 minutes patient felt immediately better. She returned to recovery to finish out her time. Increased her recovery time to 30 minutes. No further issues.

After the injection the patient grabbed her arm and when she was asked if she was ok she didn't respond and seemed slouched down. It didn't seem like she passed out but she was slouching and not responding. She seemed like she was having convulsion that lasted less than 5 seconds. Then she calmed down and her breathing was fine. I got her to respond to me that she was awake and ok. She responded with head nods. She seemed to come to a little more after a minute and she said she was fine but I wanted to call 911. I called the paramedics. During the wait she seemed to get better, we gave her water and she was slowing starting to move around more. We asked her about any under lying issues or any problems with any vaccine before. She said no to everything. The paramedics came and took all of her vitals and she was cleared that everything was ok. She called her boyfriend and we asked him to come by to help her and give her a ride home and assist. He got here and she still didn't feel totally better. After a few more minutes I took her blood pressure and it was 87/55 and her pulse was around 60. We called 911 again because she stated she wasn't feeling well again. The paramedics came back and she had a 89/41 blood pressure with a pulse of 40. They indicated that she may be having a cardiac issue so they took her to the ER.

After the first injection, I noticed mild mouth tingling, but nothing else, did not report as it was so mild and it was more notable in retrospect.  A week after the first injection developed vertigo for the first time in my life.  This lasted about a week had mostly resolved when I got the second dose.  Immediately upon receiving the second dose I felt faint.  I went to the observation area and when the feeling got stronger, reported it.  My blood pressure was taken and although I always have normal blood pressure, it was extremely high - 195/100.  My heart was racing.  I was observed for longer because of this, and was asked to lie down.  The faint feeling and high blood pressure lasted 30 min, at which time it started to improve and was sent home.  I persisted in having bouts of feeling faint (but never fainting) in the days and weeks following, joined with shortness of breath which started the second day after the second injection. I also had the normal fever, aches and pains for 4 days.  It is now a month after the second injection, and while the faintness and vertigo are mostly gone,  I have persistent shortness of breath.  Prior to the vaccine I had an albuterol inhaler that I would use 1-5 times a year for allergies.  Almost never used it.  I began having to use it multiple times daily after the second dose of the vaccine.  I am not on a steroid inhaler.  I have never had shortness of breath like this before.  I was examined at the doctors office, not much can be seen that is wrong.   An allergist believes that I did not have an allergy because my blood pressure was high instead of low as in anaphylaxis.
LAB_DATA: I was given numerous and broad spectrum of blood tests, including blood count, thyroid, liver, kidney, histamine etc, all came back normal.

I don't know if I was given Adacel or Boostrix but I know it was a Tdap Vaccine. Approximately ~16 hours after getting my Tdap shot I started to feel symptoms of a normal immune response (fatigue, mild chills, etc). This proceeded to get much worse over the next 12 hours, resulting in a fever of 102F at 2am, approximately 36 hours after the vaccine. I have had Tdap vaccines before and never had this intense of an immune response. I am submitting this report because I had 2 doses of the Moderna COVID vaccine on 12/30/20 and 1/27/21 and what I felt after this Tdap vaccine was significantly worse than what I experienced after both of my COVID vaccines. I wonder if I got this Tdap too close to my last COVID vaccine, or if I had such a robust immune response to the COVID vaccine that now all my immune response to other vaccines are more robust as well? I am assuming the symptoms I am having (fever, chills, fatigue, body aches) are an immune response because I don't have any other respiratory symptoms or related ADE. The symptoms are decently controlled with schedule use of OTC Ibuprofen and Acetaminophen.

She got the vaccine, she had no effects, and no reaction whatsoever. The husband had no side effects either.   On 3/16/21 they were on their way to go to bed and the bedroom is upstairs and she was fine, she was in the bedroom getting ready for bed, and her husband followed 15 minutes later and when he got upstairs she was sitting in a chair next to the bed, and he noticed that when he spoke with her that she did not speak clearly back, and was very low tone, not much loudness to her speech.  He didn't think much about it, and he talked with her again and noticed that she seemed to be having some difficulty talking, but he could understand what she was saying if he paid close attention.  He then realized that something was wrong, and asked her how she felt and she said she felt strange.  She was trying to take a pair of socks off and could not reach them.  She tried to lift her leg to put one knee over the other for her to remove them and was not able to do that.  He helped her take the socks off, she wanted to put some cream on her foot and was not able to do so, which is her usual routine.  He put that on her foot while he was talking to her, and her speech was different than it was earlier.  She was wearing a turtle neck shirt and was not able to take it off to get dressed for bed.  Her husband assisted in dressing her to get ready for bed.  He was thinking that she may have been having a mini-stroke.  She tried to get up from the chair and was not able to get up on her own.  He went to try to help her to lift her and it was hard.  When she did get her bottom up off the chair she stayed in a bent position and was not able to stand up.  He put her back down on the chair and tried some more times, and ultimately able to get up and he was able to get her into the bed (the chair was next to the bed).  She could sit on the edge of the bed, but was not able to move her legs on her own to get into the bed.  He struggled to get her in the bed and was not in a mood to talk and just leaned over on one side to try to go to sleep.  He told her he was going to get the walker in the basement for her to use.  He brought up the walker and put in by the bed, and informed her that it was there, and reached to see where it was in the event that she needed to use it through the night.  She did get up around 3:15 this morning to use the bathroom and her husband asked if she needed assistance, and she said that she was able to get up and go to the bathroom, and moved her legs just slow and was able to use the walker.  She was feeling much better at that time.  She got up one more time during the night and was not in need of the walker and was back to bed.  This morning when they got up at 8:00 Am and she was back to her normal self.   She came down the steps and was like nothing had ever happened.  They called her son who works in the hospital and he told them to call us to see if there were any other people that had the same reaction.    She stated while he was giving me this information that she did not recall a lot of the events that he was telling me.
OTHER_MEDS: Temazepam, Ezetimibe, magnesium, Vitamin C, Presser vision, Losartan/HCTZ, multivitamin.

Dehydration; Orthostatic positive with liquid watery stool/continues with liquid stool; Frequent diarrhea defined as hourly stool; A spontaneous report was received from a nurse practitioner concerning a 48-years-old female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced dehydration, frequent diarrhea defined as hourly stool, orthostatic positive with liquid watery stool/continues with liquid stool.  The patient had a history of colon cancer with a colon resection. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.  On 04 Feb 2021, prior to the onset of the events the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot: not provided) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 06 Feb 2021, the patient had frequent diarrhea defined as hourly stool. On 09 Feb 2021, she was hospitalized for 48 hours due to dehydration. She was doing fine. On 13 Feb 2021, despite the medications she was back to orthostatic positive with liquid watery stool. On 08 Mar 2021, patient continued with liquid stool. Treatment included cholestyramine, fiber, loperamide hydrochloride.  The seriousness criterion for the event dehydration was hospitalization.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown.   The outcome of the event of dehydration was resolved on an unknown date in Feb 2021. The outcome of the event, frequent diarrhea defined as hourly stool was considered as resolved. The outcome of the event, orthostatic positive with liquid watery stool/continues with liquid stool was not resolved.  The reporter did not provide an assessment for the events dehydration, frequent diarrhea defined as hourly stool, orthostatic positive with liquid watery stool/continues with liquid stool.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Further information has been requested.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Colectomy; Colon cancer

SYMPTOM_TEXT: She is very active in her daily life as she continues to train race horses. She reports she had been feeling well. She received her 2nd COVID vaccine on 2/22/2021. On 3/3/2021 she began feeling achy, foods no longer tasted good to her, over the next day or so she developed nausea with dry heaves, diarrhea, and burning with urination. She then stopped eating. She has a dry non-productive cough. She denies any melena, hematochezia, hematemesis, chest pain, fevers, chills, shortness of breath. She is now complaining of generalized weakness. She denies any abdominal pain, but admits to some tenderness in the right side of her back. She denies any known ill contacts. She and her Husband mostly stay at home since COVID began. She reports they have not even traveled with the horses since COVID started.  3/15/21 In the ED she was found to have a right pyelonephritis, acute kidney injury, elevated LFT's, leukocytosis. She had an abdominal CT that showed concern for dilated CBD. She went later for a gallbladder US. This showed no dilations of CBD.   3/16/2021: Today there was a significant improvement in leukocytes. Her blood pressure has dropped and is low to low normal. She continues to feel generalized weakness. She is eating ice chips and tried a jello this morning that she has kept down. She denies any further diarrhea or active vomiting overnight. She denies any abdominal pain, but does have tenderness to the epigastric area with palpation.  Creatinine is unchanged this morning. I gave an IV fluid bolus this morning to support BP. She does continue to have the dry cough. She reports she had a rash to her right arm around the COVID injection site that was itchy for a couple of days. It has resolved. She denies any other rashes, joint inflammation or redness. She denies any shortness of breath.   Eosinophilia, with 1600 AEC. Concerning for possible delayed hypersensitivity to COVID vaccine. Will continue to trend. Cough non-productive. Continue to monitor respiratory status/sx. CRP. LDH, ESR, and CRP added on to labs. Will draw D-dimer tomorrow morning as well.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: March 13, 2021-1:30pm-Shot administered to right arm-it bled and the nurse had to apply pressure with an alcohol swab. It stopped immediately. 1:40-started feeling a tightness in the muscle in my neck under my right ear Stayed a few minutes longer than the required 15 to see if anything else presented. Mentioned it to the nurse and rep. The rep asked if I was nervous about getting the shot. When I said yes, he said it may just be that. Told me to contact my doctor with additional issues.  1:55-When leaving the parking lot, I felt my lips and nostril on the right side go numb-it felt like when Novocain is wearing off after a dentist visit. As the day progressed, the area under my ear and down my neck got more and more sensitive. My lips continued to feel numb. My injection site was tender and black and blue. When I went to bed at 9pm, I began experiencing lots of pain in my right lower jaw. I took a Tylenol but it didn't alleviate the pain. I called on-call doctor. Since I already had taken a Tylenol, he suggested an anti-inflammatory and warm moist compresses and to contact him again if things worsened. 3/14/21-7:00am-Upon awaking, my jaw pain was virtually gone but the whole area I had had the issue with was very tender to the touch. My lip still felt a bit numb.  3:25pm- It is now 26 hours since my vaccination. I still feel like I had trauma to the right side of my face and neck because it is sensitive to the touch. I also have a continued slight sensitivity of my lips on the right side. My glands on both sides of my neck now seem tender, as well. 3/15/21-3/17/21-I continue to have random pain/tenderness in the aforementioned areas. I also have an aura of tingling in my brain from time to time.
OTHER_MEDS: Provastatin 20mg., calcium, vit e,vit c, flaxseed oil, D3, Aller-fex allergy medicine, Trunature Digestive Probiotic Gummies

Patient was noted to have abrupt respiratory failure 2 days after taking the 1st dose. The patient was admitted to the hospital for acute respiratory failure with hypoxemia secondary to acute CHF exacerbation. The patient had a transthoracic echocardiogram performed 2 weeks prior to hospitalization that was noted to show a left ventricular ejection fraction of 60-65%. At the hospitalization, her left ventricular ejection fraction was noted to decrease to 25-30%. Left heart catheterization was performed and showed no signs of ischemic heart disease (coronary artery disease). Patient was started on Entresto 24/26mg PO BID and Toprol XL 50mg PO daily and was diuresed with Bumex 1mg IV daily and was noted to have improvement in respiratory symptoms for which she was weaned off of BiPAP 15/5 with FiO2 of 50% down to room air. Patient had repeat transthoracic echocardiogram ordered prior to discharge and was noted to have an improvement in left ventricular ejection fraction to 48% prior to discharge. The only change was that the patient had the COVID-19 vaccination. Patient does not have any history of coronary artery disease or heart failure. Patient was worked up extensively for other etiologies of heart failure and none were found.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Started feeling itchiness on the injection site on 3-14-21 (day 7 after the shot) off and on, but mostly off.  Nothing troublesome.  Today, morning of 3-17-21 (day 10 after shot), I felt a slightly stronger itch and noticed a slight pinkish rash at injection site about 3" long and  2" wide tapering at the top and bottom.  As the day continued, the stronger itchiness grew more frequent and rash slightly bigger and redder/more noticeable.  Finally had to put some hydrocortisone cream for some relief, but so far it's not really troublesome.  No pain thank goodness.  This happened to me before, 3 years ago, a week after I got my Shingrix vaccine shot (which had a much bigger, redder, raised rash).  When I read about the rashes happening to some people after the Moderna shot, the description was exactly like my post-Shingrix shot rash, but fortunately I had no pain, just itchiness, a little warm to the touch.  So, I was expecting that I'd probably get the rash and sure enough I have.  That's it so far with this current rash after my first dose of Moderna vaccine.  I treated the rash after the Shingrix  shot with just hydrocortisone cream occasionally (I don't recall having to resort to taking an antihistamine) and the rash and itchiness went away gradually after about 2-3 days. Obviously, I'm hoping the same thing will happen with this rash.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The following is the timeline of progression: First 48 hours: Immediately following the vaccine I felt I would vomit. That lasted 2 hours. The remainder of the 48 hours I had a growing headache that turned into a migraine level. Cognitively my husband would say I was out of it, not able to focus. The area around my eyes � my eyelids and below eyelids bright red � like I had put a bright red blush on them. Three to four days later: Saturday night my symptoms started to progress over a span of a few hours very drastically. I had symptoms of Diarrhea� crazy impact in my gut. Sunday I still had migraine level pain in a headache. I felt increased symptoms of nausea and diarrhea increased. Sunday I still had migraine level pain in a headache.  I felt increased symptoms of nausea and diarrhea increased. By Sunday afternoon I had full blown symptoms of stomach flu. I had chills, extreme nausea that became debilitating. We do not have a thermometer that works, as a result I do not know if I had a fever. By Sunday night I was vomiting and symptoms progressed to tightness of chest, shortness of breath, vomiting, diarrhea, chills. My gut was literally moving in sharp pain, sounds, and cramping. It was severe diarrhea. I was achy and tired, but could not fall asleep due to nausea and vomiting. I was unable to stand up without the fear of passing out. I tried to manage the nausea with medicine that I have at home. It assisted but did not ultimate make an impact. By 4:30 a.m. I was scared by the lack of breath and asked my husband to call 911. The paramedic stated that I had an increased heart rate, but good blood pressure. I went to the hospital and received fluids, two different additional doses of nausea medicine, oxygen and a gut muscle relaxer. After 30 to 40 minutes I showed improvement and was able to go home. Still had pink color tone in skin around my eyes. On that Monday (2/8/2021), I was unable to go to work and called in for Covid PTO. I slept most of the day. Five days later: Still have a headache that can be managed with Tylenol. I still have diarrhea. I no longer have nausea, the pink color around my eyes seems to be gone.The nurse team and ambulance team all stated that the second shot was awful. Three folks stated they were in fetal position for two days. I was not able to ask what that meant due to my extreme nausea and trying to not dry heave. Note: I did not have any symptoms from the first vaccine � just a dull headache.
LAB_DATA: Blood test was taken to confirm nothing else was wrong, anti-nausea to help stop vomiting and Dicyclomine for abdominal pain, I also had an IV
CUR_ILL: Microscopic Colitis and had a bacterial overgrowth

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After receiving the first dose of the Pfizer vaccine, my face immediately went all red and got hot.  I stayed at the pharmacy for 30 minutes to ensure I didn't have an allergic reaction like a breathing issue.  I had my epi pen with me just in case.  It was loud in the pharmacy so I didn't notice it at first but once I got outside and was in the car, my ears were ringing.  When we got to the restaurant to eat, we were the only family in there and it was pretty quiet.  The ringing was really high pitched and loud.  For the following two weeks it did not stop, day and night.  I contacted my primary and had a telehealth appt and also went physically in to my ENT's office.  I also tried acupuncture to see if that would take away the ringing.  The acupuncture seemed to lower the pitch in my ear but it was still present.  2 hours after I left the office the pitch was back to a high pitch ring again.  I cancelled my appointment today for 3/18 for the second dose because no one can assure me that this ear ringing will go away and the doctor's are unsure of whether the second dose will trigger a worse condition.  I had a hearing test on 3/16 at my ENT's office and I couldn't hear some of the sounds because of the ear ringing but I did pass the test at the very line of baseline normal.  My ENT is unsure if I will lose hearing due to this vaccine.
LAB_DATA: ENT appt on 3/1/2021 to visually look at my ears.  Telehealth appt with my Primary doctor on 3/10 (she recommended the acupuncture).  Acupuncture appt on 3/13 to try and get rid of the ringing.  Hearing test at my ENT's office on 3/16.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got my vaccination at 4pm, waited the 15 minutes at the united center waiting area and felt fine.  I went home to pickup my daughter and at 6pm was back on the road driving and started to feel tired.  I stopped at the light at foster and had just called my parents to tell them i had gotten the shot.  I mentioned I was starting to feel tired and as I said it started to feel more tired.  My mom responded maybe you should pull over and that was the last thing i remember as I fainted/blacked out immediately after.  When I awoke my daughter (in the back seat along with my dog) explained that I had  accelerated and hit the back of another car and then drove around that car, ending with both cars facing the direction of travel with my car in front of the car i had rear-ended.  I was completely disoriented and had not recollection of hitting the gas or break much less driving.  I was told two times that the driver in the other car was fine and was told when asked a third time that he did have some pain possibly and went in the ambulance to get checked out.  I felt disoriented and jittery last night, took 2 Tylenol before bed and have felt fine today beyond feeling confused and horrible about what happen. My husband picked me up form the site and took me to my parents a few blocks north of the accident.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Administered Moderna to client at 17years and 10 months.

Approximately 7-8 minutes after receiving the vaccine, started to feel light-headed, thought she was going to pass out, and her heart was racing extremely high. The health care team at the site took her blood pressure, measured heart rate, gave her water, juice and chocolate and tried to get her heart rate to drop. It was fluctuating up and down and she couldn't stand up without dizziness;  we waited 45 minutes and then drove her home as she was unable to drive her own car.  She was experiencing significant lightheadedness, and consistent heart racing even while lying down on the sofa/bed. This continued for several days and she stayed home from school and sports. We called her primary care doctor on the 10th and they suggested she wait another day to see how she was feeling. She started to feel a bit better by Friday, was still experiencing a bit of the tiredness, nauseous, light-headed and heart spikes, but was able to drive, move around.  On Sunday evening, she started to experience increased heart rate again, lymph nodes were very painful and started experiencing the light headedness all evening.  On Monday we took her to her primary care provider and they then referred her to ER for the heart racing and a EKG. The increased light headedness, feeling like she will pass out even while laying in bed, dizziness has all increased and her lymph nodes continue to be swollen and painful. It has been over a week since the vaccine and there is no clear sign of her reaction getting any better, if not worse.  The EKG results indicated a new abnormality and we are trying to get her to a cardiologist.  She is and had been a very healthy, varsity athlete that runs over 30 hours a week with track, and since receiving the first dose of the Moderna vaccine is unable to move very far within the house without feeling that she is going to pass out or that her heart rate is shooting up uncontrollably.
LAB_DATA: EKG test given at the ER on Monday Mar 15.  Cardiologist reported results were abnormal but we have not yet had an appointment to get specifics. Urine test.

Onset of symptoms was about 9  to 10 hours after receiving the vaccine.  Started out with mild muscle soreness. This progressed while I was sleeping to become quite extreme. I woke up at 1:00am  (10 hours after vaccine) to fever, chills, muscle soreness in entirety of body and pain/aching joints. When I got up to get some Tylenol my body began shaking uncontrollably. I would describe this as muscle tremors. It was quite vigorous to the point where all my muscles  were very tight and felt like stone. I quickly took a Benadryl (25mg) paired with Tylenol (500mgs) to battle the reaction.   I laid back down to try and stop the tremors but they continued for a good fifteen minutes or so until the medications started to work. Afterward I felt much better. The muscle tremors stopped completely, but I continued to have chills, fever, and aching joints well into the next day. Fatigue was extreme and I slept on and off for about 24 hours. After the initial 24 hours period, all symptoms went away and I was 100% back to normal.
LAB_DATA: I did not seek medical attention for the reaction.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 12 hours after getting the second Moderna dose, while trying to sleep, my heart rate was 100-110, with the feeling of repeated PVCs in my heart.  I knew this feeling because I had dealt with episodes of repeated PVCs (and later PACs) from about 2016 to February 2020.  After being in the hospital in February 2020 for life-threatening sepsis, pneumonia, and strep, the arrhythmias stopped completely.  I had been trying to control the episodes by taking atenolol 25mg/d; upon realizing that the PVC episodes had stopped, I terminated the medication.  So at about 1AM on 3/7/2021 or so, I noticed the PVCs and the rapid heart rate and could not sleep.  Fever went up to 102.4, thirsty and possibly dehydrated. Went to ER at 7am.  Tests showed repeated PVCs.  Kidney function was slightly abnormal.  Started taking atenolol through Tuesday, 3/9.  Heart monitor halter showed PVCs continued through Tuesday.  By Thursday, 3/11, it was apparent that the PVCs had stopped and heart rate was normal.  I stopped the atenolol and the irregular heartbeat has not returned.
LAB_DATA: EKD 12-LEAD, 3/7/21, 8:35AM: Sinus Tachycardia w/occasional premature Vent. complexes; otherwise normal ECG when compared w/ecg of 12/17/20; PVCs are now present; pulse incr by 41BPM.  Halter Heart monitor worn 3/7-3/9 (48 hours) showed irregular heart beat according to Dr.
OTHER_MEDS: Levothyroxine 75mcg/d, L-Theanine 200mg/d, Pravastatin 40mg/d, Probiotic; Prebiotic; Life Extension Foundation Mix (multivitamin); CoEnzyme Q10 100mg/d
HISTORY: 2016 to Feb 2020: irregular heartbeat (PVCs/PACs).  PVCs were primary issue.  Took atenolol 25mg/d for it.  When I got sepsis, pneumonia, strep and was in hospital at  in Feb 2020 - after i got out, the arrhythmias stopped until I got the second Moderna covid dose.
PRIOR_VAX: first Moderna covid vaccine - 100 fever, migraine headache (see above)

Patient is a 74 Y male with a past medical history of  hypertension, paroxysmal atrial flutter, COPD, diabetes mellitus type 2, schizoaffective disorder, depression, pulmonary embolism, pulmonary nodules, asthma, tobacco dependence, alcohol abuse and urge incontinence  who presents to the Emergency Department today with complaints of shortness of breath and leg swelling for the past few days.  He has also been having cough which is productive of clear sputum and has been wheezing.He has been using his albuterol inhalers with relief. He has also noted increased leg swelling more and decreased urination.  He tries to be compliant with his salt and fluid restriction but does not always follow through.  He had just been hospitalized at hospital from February 21 to March 2 for COPD exacerbation, CHF and hypoxia.  Patient has a history of COVID B infection last October and was hospitalized for it.  Yesterday he got a 2nd COVID shot but denies any fever, chills, chest pain, nausea vomiting after that He presented to the ED where he was noted to have temperature of 98.4�, pulse of 76, respiration of 32, blood pressure 19477 and O2 sat of 95% on 3 liters.  Labs showed a white count of 8.8, hemoglobin 12.9, bicarb of 35, creatinine 0.57, potassium 3.6, magnesium 1.6, BNP of 2675 and 2 serial troponins of 55 and 50.  Chest x-ray with chronic vascular prominence unchanged.  Some minimal infiltrates or atelectasis at the left base are improved.  EKG with normal sinus rhythm, heart rate of 76, few PVCs and PACs. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received 1st dose shot on 01:30 PM 02/17/2021.  Arm started swelling and red blotches appeared on upper arm 1st night.  Went online to Moderna website to determine if this was normal.  Said had red blotches, call doctor.  Called on 02/18/2021.  Advised to use ice pack and Benadryl if had it.  Only had Benadryl cream.  Ice pack too painful, used ice water and wash cloth wrap.  Blotches started fading on 3rd day.  Still had swelling, pain at vaccine site diminished.  On 5th day blotches gone, itching began.  Benadryl cream helped with itching for 2 days.  Day 7 and 8 Benadryl cream stopped working, redness on upper arm became really noticeable and swelling increased.  Day 9, swelling continued & became hard, redness across upper arm above and below shot site, arm hot.  By evening decided to call doctor the next morning.  Day 10, Dr. office visit.  Dr. was not sure why this was happening, said it could have been something picked up on needle before shot given as there was internal infection and skin infection. He prescribed antibiotics and gave me an antibiotic shot.  Started meds as directed.  Day 11 skin redness became a raised welt and started crawling down my arm.  Arm swelling made skin tight and arm was still hot.  Day 12 welt almost to my elbow.  No pain only sensitive to touch and itching continued.  Day 13 doctor?s office visit again because of increased symptoms.  Doctor started looking at other causes, gave me an additional stronger oral antibiotic and another more potent antibiotic shot.  Day 14 another doctor?s office visit to see if there was any improvement.  Skin welt crawl had stopped to elbow, but there was still some on upper arm but smaller, swelling and hot had diminished.  Days 15-16, swelling diminished more, welt crawl stopped and redness decreased.  Day 17, last doctor?s office visit.  Little red around the edges only.  Arm discolored where welt had been.  Doctor had by then determined that my immune system had gone into overdrive on the COVID vaccine received.  He advised me not to get the second dose shot or I could have an even more intense reaction.  Days 18-22.  Welt gone, still discoloration but much lighter.  Finished antibiotics. Still have some itching (intermittent). (THIS IS THE 3RD ATTEMPT OVER THE LAST 2 WEEKS TO ENTER THIS INFO).  As of 03/17/2021 still experiencing some affects.
LAB_DATA: 03/16/2021, - a urine culture is being performed.
OTHER_MEDS: Levothyroxine; Atenolol; Krill Oil; Calcium; D3, B1, Magnesium, Multi-Vitamin

SYMPTOM_TEXT: (1) Skin lesions won't heal.  (2) Blood won't clot.  (3) Minor symptoms similar to a head cold.  Vaccination dates: 1/28/2021, 3/2/2021.  During February, I was experiencing high work stress (writing software).  When I am stressed, I scratch spots of keratosis on my arms.  During February, this behavior remarkably resulted in small lesions blossoming into circular lesions the size of a quarter.  These lesions were many (about 6 on left arm alone), large, wet and open sores, painful, and would not heal.  At one point, I had 6 sores on my left arm, several on my right, a painful sore on my right buttocks, two painful sores behind my ear, a sore at the base of my neck in back, and a very painful sore on my scrotum, plus a huge blood blister on my lower lips.  As I was enduring all of this, I also had severe sores within my nose that bled profusely.  All of this was very painful and very unusual.  Nothing like this had ever happened before to me.  I treated the worst of these sores with Neosporin and bandages.  They have improved, but not healed entirely yet.   All of this was initiated by my stress and scratching behavior.  But I am convinced that the extreme results must be due to the vaccines, which seem to have interfered with the healing, made the sores get very large and infected, and kept my blood from clotting.  There has been significant improvement, but I have not yet recovered from this.
OTHER_MEDS: Imatinib mesylate 400mg / day.  (Adjuvant chemotherapy for GIST resected in 2015.)
ALLERGIES: None.  (Imatinib mesylate suppresses my former food allergies.)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I suffered a heart attack on March 11, 2021, at approx 145pm, while sitting at my desk - WFH.  My symptoms were sweats, nausea, followed by chest pains beginning on the left side of my chest; sweats and nausea subsided for approx 1 hr, returning again, followed by chest pains radiating  the across the full chest approx.  I left my desk at the onset to wash my face, returning to my desk to talk a scheduled phone call at 2pm, lasting until 3pm.  I left desk to walk outside to take in some fresh air, my wife ask me if I was ok, I said no.  She ask if I was having a heart attack, to which I replied, I don't know.  shortly there after we left for the ER at arriving approx 4pm.  At that point ER staff did a quick assessment, taking my to an ER patient room where i was advised by the attending Dr that they thought I was having a heart attack.  Shortly thereafter I was taking to the Cath lab where a stent was insert and then taken to ICU.  Where I remained until I was released on 3/12/2021 at 3pm.  There was no detectable heart damage and I was placed a regime of blood thinner, a beta blocker and cholesterol med.  I do not have high blood pressure, high cholesterol or history of heart problems.  My last physical was Feb 2021.
LAB_DATA: All necessary tests were performed on 3/11/2021 at the Hospital.  I had 100% blockage in an inferior artery.
HISTORY: Takes Levothyroxine, 175 MG for thyroid condition.  Has since early 1990's

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Began with extreme fatigue. Within a couple of hours developed shortness of breath walking up stairs (never an issue prior) and palpitations. 01/26-walked to my gyno appointment two blocks away. After 20 minutes of rest had elevated blood pressure of 148/90, never had an issue w/ blood pressure. Woke up everyday with palpitations, shortness of breath and a headache that would last 10-15 minutes (not similar to any of my previous migraines). My palpitations and shortness of breath worsened over time and I started to feel them while lying flat or even slight movements such as standing up. My fatigue was pretty unbearable. I would need to take several naps a day and even then I never felt fully rested. I received my 2nd dose 02/27 and my symptoms increased in frequency and intensity. I was having more episodes a day and even walking within my own home I was out of breath. I went to the hospital and they were not able to find a cause for immediate danger so I was sent home. Originally they thought possible autoimmune issue such as Rheumatoid arthritis or lupus (prior to my RF, C-proteins and sedimentation rate results). My symptoms worsened from that visit; I began experiencing episodes of light headedness, brain fog, almost loss of consciousness, numbness in hands, muscle weakness, joint pain in knee, ankles and wrists. I am at a point now where even talking I can get out of breath or while showering I have difficulty breathing. Recently my brain fogs have become more frequent and noticeable. I have started seeing a cardiologist and am getting echo, exercise test and had a halter monitor placed, but still waiting on the results. During that visit the cardiologist noticed a slight aortic murmur, which was not present prior to this situation  This is has been completely debilitating to the point where I am on temporary leave from medical school.

A week after my vaccine my neck was swollen around the collar bone in the front. It was a ball the size of the marble that was painful. I was advised to see a physician. They advised Ibuprofen to bring the swelling down and that it might take two weeks to come down. The lump stayed for a week and it only felt painful for three days. The same thing happened with the second dose which was in the other arm  and the swelling was on the other side because I got the shot in the other arm. I also had a fever nausea and body aches for two days.

As I pulled up for the 15 minute wait period the symptoms started 5 minutes after I received my vaccine.  A tingling feeling up my left arm to back of my neck. My neck stiffened and then my throat started to close.  Not to where I can't swallow but just like when I eat food that I'm allergic too, it closes up. The nurse that was overseeing me was holding the umbrella over my car window with the rainfall.  All of a sudden their was lightning & thunder. The nurse threw the umbrella because she was shocked from the lightning. She started to talk to all the other around her and forgot about me. Since I could still swallow I didn't get her attention. When she returned she asked me the time so I had to pull my phone out. She didn't know the time of my 15 minutes and sent me away. As soon as I got out of the parking area but still inside amusement park, I started to feel my cheeks becoming numb and my right eye was blurry.  I quickly moved over to the side lane still inside of amusement park and waited.  I called my husband and told him that with the heavy rain I didn't feel safe driving with my right eye being blurry.  I waiting another 15 minutes before driving home.  That evening the blurriness came back, my eye's & forehead was tender to touch but no headache.  Only pressure in my head.  My symptoms of closed throat, swollen cheeks, pressure in my head and blurriness continued on Friday, March 12th, Saturday, March 13th, Sunday, March 14th and Monday, March 15th.  As of today, no other systems other than feeling my body has inflammation.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Severe allergic reactions: Dizziness, tingling on my face and/or body and trembling. Wednesday: My arm started to feel slightly sore within minutes after the injection. On the drive home I felt allergic tingling in my body around the chest area on and off for a few minutes.  I had a strong headache that would come and go that evening. An existing itchiness on my scalp from an allergy response to a new shampoo and other products became inflamed with excessive itchiness and redness all over my scalp. I felt light headed, too. Thursday: I woke up to an itchy scalp and tingling on my forehead. I felt very dizzy all day. I still had a strong headache that would come and go. I was lethargic and slept in the afternoon. My arm was really sore. I woke up at 11:30 p.m. very nauseous. I was able to prevent vomiting by laying a certain way in my bed. Friday: I am still dizzy but not as bad as Thursday. My arm felt better today. My body is experiencing a tingling feeling all over. It was a very strange sensation. I still had a strong headache that would come and go.  Saturday: I had strong dizziness all day on Saturday. I felt awful. I called and reported my symptoms to Dr office. Sunday: My face was tingling in the morning. My left cheek felt puffy. My face is sensitive to touch. Monday:  I woke up at 3:30 a.m. and my lips felt puffy but didn?t look puffy. Arms and chest looked a little pink. At 10:20 a.m. my face felt tingly. I was also shaky and a little dizzy. I called the doctor's office and left a message. Tuesday:  I woke up with a headache and my scalp aching. My face felt tingly. There were some places on my face felt rough (sand papery) to the touch. I was still trembling. I had on and off dizziness. I made an appointment with the doctor for the next day. Wednesday: I had a video appointment with Dr. We scheduled me to have extensive bloodwork done the next day. I continued to experience tingling and trembling through February 27th.  I felt bad for ten days. I have had occasional tingling up to March 17th.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On March 16, I was sitting in a chair next to my kitchen counter when I felt like my body was being thrown.  My head was thrown forward and I hit the counter hard and sustained a large contusion above my left eye.  The room was spinning and I was dizzy for the next few hours.  I never lost consciousness but had no control of my body for the few seconds of the episode.  The episode was sudden and violent and I was just sitting when it happened.   I spoke with my physician who diagnosed me with having experienced a Tumarkin otolithic crisis.  He has instructed me to wear a helmet and not to leave my home.  He is also recommending that I have a labyrinthectomy to treat the symptoms.  While I have a history of vertigo, I have not had any dizziness for more than a year.   I now feel dizzy on and off most of the day.

It has been 6 weeks since my 2nd dose of the Moderna vaccine for Covid-19. For the first 3-4 days I had the usual moderate flu-like symptoms:  dizziness, headaches, fatigue, chills, soreness at vaccine siteetc.  Days 5-7 I seemed to gradually improve. On day 8 all of the symptoms returned with greater severity: this time I had a fever, the chills were much more intense, the headaches were excruciating, body and joint aches all over the place--I couldn't sleep or focus on anything cognitively taxing.  Interestingly, my brother, who was vaccinated just after me, also had more severe side effects beginning on day 8 post 2nd dose. He improved after 3-4 days, but my recovery has been much much lengthier. By day 14 I was still feeling very ill, though the fever did subside.  Sometime in the third week the pain in my arm at the vaccination site returned, then became intermittent, and still bothers me from time to time. I also started getting muscle spasms in the same exact locations that sent me to the ER after my probably bout with Covid in the spring of 2020. Thankfully these lasted only a week or so, though I began feeling muscle soreness in different parts of my body, ever changing. By the 4th week I was slightly better and down to 4 main symptoms: chills (by far the worst of the symptoms--to the point at which my skin would feel like it was being frostbitten by dry ice every time I changed sweaty clothes), occasional splitting headaches, and muscle soreness that included both the injection site on my arm and other areas.  I had other symptoms as well, fatigue and brain fog, etc, but these were present before the vaccination, though not as severe.
LAB_DATA: So far the only medical tests I've done are the AAT diagnostics I referenced previously. I know it's sort of fringe medicine, but my doctor doesn't want me to take a steroid unless absolutely necessary because of my medical history.  As I said I did AAT on 3/8/21 through 3/12/21, and on the 8th, 9th, and 12th I showed sensitivities to components in the vaccine. Strangely only on the 9th did it show an IgE response--the rest were sensitivities.
OTHER_MEDS: Day of vaccination: Modafinil, Dufloxetine, Malate, D-Ribose, Bovine Derived Serum IgG, Probiotic, Licorice root extract, Vitamin D Day before vaccination: I may have taken a Zyrtec, Melatonin, and low dose of THC/CBD oil.
CUR_ILL: After my first Moderna dose on 1/10/21 I had much milder and short-lived flu-like symptoms, but other than those I had no illnesses (besides my chronic conditions) within one month prior.
HISTORY: since age 13:  Chronic Fatigue Syndrom / ME Neurally Mediated Hypotension Fibromyalgia Exercise-Induced Asthma Mood disorder: Depression / Generalized Anxiety ADHD Irritable Bowel / Leaky Gut Syndrome  since 2019 (and probably long before) Herpes 1 presenting as Herpes Esophagitis (occurred first in 2019 and then once again in March 2020) HPV presenting as genital warts  since 2020  my bout of Herpes Esophagitis may have come in conjunction with contracting Covid-19. This was early in the pandemic and it was difficult to get a test until more than 10 days after my symptoms began. But I was in NYC up until March 13 and was definitely exposed to the virus. Since then I have had symptoms of "Long Covid" which strongly resembled my CFS/ME symptoms, and were as severe as when I was a teenager. This included fatigue, dizziness brain fog, muscle and joint pain, insomnia, swollen lymph nodes, etc. New symptoms includes muscle spasms and tachycardia.
PRIOR_VAX: but just moderate side effects from the annual flu vaccine--never for more than a week.
ALLERGIES: medications: none allergies / sensitivities to foods (not necessarily a true IgE): constantly changing, but lately has included eggs, dairy, shellfish, peanuts, other roasted nuts, some sugars, molds and fungi * on 3/8/21 I began 5 days of non-traditional allergy and sensitivity testing using AAT. Among other things it showed I was having both a true IgE response and other sensitivities to vaccine components. These changed from day-to-day throughout the week.

I received the first dose of the Pfizer vaccine on February 25, 2021 at approximately 9:30 AM.  About 2 hours later I began to sneeze quite frequently.  About 3 1/2 hours after the shot hives began to break out on both my hands.  Later, during the early evening hours I began to sneeze more rapidly and repeatedly.  I also began blowing my nose repeatedly due to the massive amount of mucous my body was producing. I became very sick with a cold and stayed in the bed Friday (2-26-2021) through Monday (3-1-21).  I also began breaking out in hives on the back of my neck in patches and individual hives over various parts of my body. I went to a  Medical clinic on Tuesday (3-2-21) and was given Zyrtec. Feeling much worse the next day (3-3-21) I went to the Medical clinic and received a COVID test (both the rapid and PCR tests  were negative.  I was prescribed cough medicine and given a steroid shot.  My symptoms persisted after this visit and did not get better.  Particularly, my cough became extremely bad.  I coughed so much my throat became sore from the coughing and became nauseated.  Also, a patch of hives had surfaced under my chin.  I returned to the Medical clinic on March 12th.  I was given a COVID rapid test and a Flu test.  Both were negative.  The chest x-ray was also clear.  I was prescribed the following medications during the March 12th visit:  Albuterol Sulfate Inhaler, Azithromycin pack, Virtussin cough medicine, and sudafed.  My symptoms subsided somewhat, but the cough remained relentless.  I want to a Primary Care Physician on March 16th and was prescribed a Methylprednisolone (6-day steroid) pack.  I also made an appointment to see an Allergist.  I was diagnosed with Asthma and was prescribed Symbicort, fluticasone, and levocetirizine.  The Allergist advised that I continue with the steroid pack as well.  Please note, I have never been diagnosed with or suffered from allergies or asthma prior to taking the vaccine shot.
LAB_DATA: 3-2-21: COVID Rapid and PCR tests negative / Chest x-ray clear/ Negative flu test/No fever 3-12-21:  Flu test negative / Rapid COVID test negative / Chest x-ray clear/No fever

Family call Clinical Lead to car for elderly woman in backseat of car who had become unresponsive.   Patient lying on side. Wearing portable NC o2.  Unresponsive to verbal/sternal rub. No pulse, No resps.   Called AMR to car side who called 911. Transferred patient to a gurney and began CPR as we transferred to AMR rig.   EKG - showed PEA - CPR continued - patient intubated by AMR - epi is given.   Pt transported by AMR/Fire to hospital.    Pt was a full code on Hospice - she passed away 3/11/21 with the following cause of death: 1.Acute-on-chronic hypoxemic/hypercarbic respiratory failure, multifactorial in origin.  2. Possible aspiration pneumonia, present on admission.  3. Bronchiectasis, chronic, secondary to asbestosis.  4. Acute combined metabolic and toxic encephalopathy, present on admission.  5. Out of hospital pulseless electrical activity arrest.  6. Hyperkalemia.  7. Cardiogenic shock.  8. Acute kidney injury.  9. Lactic acidosis.  10. Acute diastolic congestive heart failure.  11. Severe protein-calorie malnutrition.
CUR_ILL: PMHx: 02 use for chronic pneumonia and Ascending Aortic Aneurysm  - on Hospice Full Code
HISTORY: PMHx: 02 use for chronic pneumonia and Ascending Aortic Aneurysm

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 3:56pm- 71/F in post vaccination area witnessed multiple episodes of vomiting yellow emesis. Appears diaphoretic, initial BP 220/110, HR 110. O2 95%, RR 22. Pt received the vaccine at 3:46pm. She denies blurred vision, no headache, no chest pain or SOB. Denies abdominal pain but her daughter states she recently had a hernia repair and has had issues with cyclic vomiting induced with certain foods or stress, which her doctors are monitoring her for. Her daughter states she was feeling sick before she got her vaccine. Patient states she took her morning medication at 7am, had some breakfast at 10am and states she feels it was some pineapple she ate that caused her to start feeling nauseous. She adds that she is taking several blood pressire medications but when she begins to vomting her blood pressure "gets really high." Pt is AOx4, able to speak in clear complete sentences.  4:05pm- BP 210/120, HR 82, 97%, RR 24. Pt continues to vomit intermittently but states she is starting to feel better. Onsite nurse manager, lead and site lead aware. EMS services requested. 4:10pm- BP 191/100, HR 86,  96%. No vomiting witnessed. 4:14pm- Ems arrives on scene. BP sitting 156/91, standing 140/92. Pt states she feels better. Parameduc offers to transfer her to the hospital but patient declines. Her daughter is at side and she states she would rather her daughter take her home since she is feeling better. Educated regarding when to seek medical attention. Pt AOx4, resp even, skin warm and dry, not actively vomiting, speaks in clear complete sentences. Assisted to POV via wheelchair. Pt in no apparent distress.
CUR_ILL: Post sx vomiting (hernia repair) only occurs intermittently but no fever, URI or respiratory illness

No medications Allergies reviewed   HR 94 with strong radial pulses RR 16 Alert and oriented, Pink warm dry - Mild raised erythematous wheals just inferior to bilateral earlobes. Nothing over anterior neck. No chest or back involvement. RRR with normal S1 and S2 Lungs CTAB   Likely mild allergic reaction. Patient requested to take own Benadryl, and took 25 mg PO Benadryl. She was observed for an additional 20 minutes with improving symptoms and no further progression of rash.    Patient reported feeling much better, and was accompanied by both parents (both RNs). She also was in possession of her Epi-Pen. Reviewed the signs and symptoms of anaphylaxis. Reviewed the indications for taking Epi-Pen. Reminded the patient that if she used her Epi-Pen OR if she was feeling worse in any way, I would strongly recommend evaluation in the Emergency Department. Reviewed that if she needed Epi-Pen, she should call 9-1-1 for immediate care and transport.    Patient and parents expressed verbal understanding and agreement prior to leaving the vaccination site at patient request. (Patient was not the vehicle driver.)

Five minutes after the shot I felt lightheaded and funny. Then my heart started to beat hard.  It didn't last too long and by the time I told the nurse she checked my pulse and said it was strong but normal. They watched me for 30 min. I felt better, but ever since then I have had flutterings of the heart.  I called my doctor who said it was nerves and to take the second shot. About ten days later I went to Urgent care who did a electrocardiogram and said it was normal, they didn't catch the flutterings.  They told me it was nerves and to take the second shot. 14 days after the shot I took Claritin D which seemed to calm the heart.  I am taking it every day now, until I'm sure the flutterings are gone.  I'm pretty sure I had an allergic reaction and I will not be taking the second shot unless you can assure me I should. I called my doctor again and was told they weren't seeing sick people, go to a heart specialist, although they didn't recommend one.

It soon became clear that he was having an anaphylactic reaction. we called for an ambulance,  we administered one dose of an Epipen, and administered oxygen. His pulse ox was in the low 80's.   within a minute or two, he started to react and started to moan, breathe more normally, then began to speak to us.  His BP was checked and was 118/83. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had some sort of reaction to the vaccine about 1-2 minutes after receiving it, and it was super scary and they had to call the paramedics.   After the pharmacist injected me, I felt the arm pain right away. No big deal. I walked over to the chair to sit for my 15 minutes. I was happy to be vaccinated and kind of saw it as my mini booster for my immune system that already beat COVID-19. As I sat there, the only thing I could say is, I felt a tingling cold sensation moving from my arm through me. Almost like I could feel the vaccine moving through my system. The tingling kept moving and I thought to myself, okay cool. I guess it's working. Awesome. But then my head felt cold, I felt tingling in my head, my mouth tasted like metal, saliva started to build in my mouth, I started to sweat, I felt overly sweaty all over my body, but my head felt cold and tingly.   I was staring straight ahead and everything started to go staticky, like a television set, and the static began to build and started to get starry. Everything in my vision started to fade. So I spoke out to say something weird was happening.  A man came over to talk to me and hold me up. He kept saying stuff but then my ears started ringing and I couldn't hear him anymore. I began to fade out as the stars got more intense. Then, as if it was just a mini reboot, my brain started to come back online and the picture in front of me began to fade back into view. I felt nauseous and still had a super metal taste in my mouth. They called the paramedics to give me a checkup. The metal taste in my mouth stayed the longest, but after about 45 minutes I felt well enough to go home.  On and off, I have this intense tingling inside my brain. It reminds me of a time when I was in the hospital on morphine. Just a tingling pins and needles sensation inside my head. Other than that, I am okay now. But I'm concerned it's some sort of reaction because I already had COVID-19.

Client waited in Observation Area and was observed by EMT to have blotchiness in both hands 15 minutes later. Client also stated to EMT her "throat  feels tight and dry." EMT alerted Lead RN  while EMT took vitals at 3:25pm. Vitals: BP: 110/80, HR: 125 bpm, O2 sat: 96%. Upon assessment of client, Lead RN authorized EMT to administer 50mg of Diphenhydramine HCL oral solution per protocol with a water bottle at 3:36pm. Another set of vitals were taken following administration of Diphenhydramine HCL oral solution. Vitals at 3:38pm: HR: 78 bpm, O2 sat: 97%. Final set of vitals were taken at 3:46pm: BP: 118/86, HR: 71 bpm, O2 sat: 96%. Client stated the initial throat tightness with dry throat and mouth subsided after administration of Diphenhydramine HCL oral solution. At 3:50pm client was educated by Lead RN & EMTs on s/sx of adverse reaction and when to go to the ED/call MD. Client left vaccine site with a steady gait at approximately 3:52pm.

Levels of TSH, among other indicators that pointed towards onset of hyperthyroidism. My doctor told me that this was acute thyroiditis. My heart rate was very high (122 bpm) when I visited my doctor's office and it was 130 bpm when I was triaged in the Emergency Room. Upon my doctor's advice, I went to the ER in the afternoon of 03/12/2021 where I was further tested. I was given medications to counteract inflammation, nausea and headache. In addition, I was given medication (beta blocker) to lower my heart rate. When my blood pressure was taken after a couple of hours, the readings revealed that my pressure had also started to fall. I spent overnight in the telemetry unit of the ER - I was given 2 liters of IV fluids to stabilize my vitals. The following day (03/13/2021), I met with endocrinologists who told me to what extent my thyroids were affected and what further medications to take. I had told them and other ER doctors as to what precipitated all of this. I was given anti inflammatory medication and a beta blocker that day before I was discharged in the evening.        I have no history of thyroid issues or heart issues. I do not suffer from any chronic illness. I was not sick before I took the second dose of the vaccine. I started to feel ill within 5 hours of taking the vaccine shot, and the symptoms worsened over nearly the following two weeks. Now, following medical intervention, I am continuing treatment with various medications. I don't feel well yet, and I understand that the process towards recovery is going to be slow and unpredictable.        I wanted to report this, since I feel that scientists and researchers should have this knowledge that thyroiditis can happen as an adverse reaction to the COVID-19 vaccine (Pfizer/BioNTech).
LAB_DATA: Doctor's office- Blood Tests, Bilateral Carotid Study Report, Trans-crannial Doppler Study Report- 03/11/2021 Blood Tests, Ultrasound of the thyroid, X ray of the lungs- 03/12/2021.  Tests on 03/12/2021 were carried out while I was in the Emergency room- Blood Reports from the Doctor's clinic as well as the Hospital revealed conditions consistent with acute thyroiditis. The ultrasound of the thyroid shows inflammation of the right thyroid lobe.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: This case involves a six-month-old male patient who received second dose of INFLUENZA QUADRIVAL A-B VACCINE [FLUZONE QUADRIVALENT] (batch number and expiry date not reported) via an intramuscular route in the left thigh for prophylactic vaccination two weeks and 1 day later instead of 4 weeks on 09-Mar-2021 (inappropriate schedule of product administration). The patient's medical history, past medical treatment(s), vaccination(s) and family history were not provided. Concomitant medications included DIPHTHERIA VACCINE TOXOID, HIB VACCINE CONJ (TET TOX), PERTUSSIS VACCINE ACELLULAR 5-COMPONENT, POLIO VACCINE INACT 3V (MRC 5), TETANUS VACCINE TOXOID (PENTACEL), PNEUMOCOCCAL VACCINE CONJ 7V (CRM197) (PREVNAR) and ROTAVIRUS VACCINE LIVE REASSORT ORAL 5V (ROTATEQ) for prophylactic vaccination. On 22-Feb-2021, the patient also received a first dose of the same vaccine (lot UT7081KA and expiry date: 30-Jun-2021) via an unknown route in an unknown administration site for prophylactic vaccination. The physician asked should the child be revaccinated. This was a case of actual medication error case due to drug dose administration interval too short (latency same day). At the time of reporting, no adverse event was reported. This suspected adverse reaction report is submitted and classified as a medication error solely and exclusively to ensure the marketing authorization holders compliance with the requirements set out in Directive 2001/83/EC and Module VI of the Good Pharmacovigilance Practices. The classification as a medical error is in no way intended, nor should it be interpreted or construed as an allegation or claim made by the marketing authorization holder that any third party has contributed to or is to be held liable for the occurrence of this medication error.

Vaccine fetal exposure during pregnancy; Preterm birth at 35.7 weeks of gestation age; This observational study case was received from other health professional on 09-Mar-2021 and concerned a male neonate, whose mother was a 32-year-old, pregnant, female subject of body weight 129 lbs, height 58 inches and body mass index (BMI) 27, enrolled in, a prospective observational safety study on pregnancy outcome in women immunized with Afluria QIV, a seasonal quadrivalent vaccine, during pregnancy.  Maternal concurrent conditions included high BMI. Maternal concomitant medication included Vitafol one (ascorbic acid, betacarotene, colecalciferol, cupric oxide, cyanocobalamin, folic acid, magnesium oxide, nicotinamide, omega-3 fatty acids, polysaccharide-iron complex, potassium iodide, pyridoxine hydrochloride, riboflavin, thiamine mononitrate, tocopheryl acetate, zinc oxide) used for healthy pregnancy.  Maternal obstetrical history included two previous pregnancies with two full term live births. The neonate's mother had no offspring with major congenital malformations (MCMs). The neonate's mother had no maternal or paternal history with MCMs. The neonate's mother did not use tobacco, alcohol or illicit drugs during pregnancy. Paternal age was not reported.  The neonate's mother's last menstrual period (LMP) date was 20-Jun-2020, the estimated delivery date (EDD) was  reported as 27-Mar-2021 and corrected estimated date of delivery (CEDD) was not reported. The type of pregnancy was multiple. The neonate's father's age was not reported.  On 02-Sep-2020, at approximately 10 weeks of gestation (calculated per LMP), the neonate's mother was vaccinated with Afluria QIV (Flu Vaccine Egg Split QIV CSL) (influenza vaccine; dose, anatomical location and  route of administration: not reported] (explicitly coded as 'Foetal exposure during pregnancy') for influenza immunisation. The batch number was P100239705.  On 16-Sep-2020, the first trimester screen and panorama test revealed no MCMs.  On 19-Oct-2020, the second trimester screen revealed increased risk of Down syndrome. No MCMs were noted.  On 23-Oct-2020, follow up amniocentesis regarding increased risk of Down syndrome revealed normal result. No MCMs were noted.  At 35.7 weeks of gestation (as reported), the mother delivered two premature live male neonates by caesarean method. The characteristics of the first neonate included: birth weight 2710 g, head circumference: 33 cm, length: 47 cm. APGAR (appearance, pulse, grimace, activity and respiration) scores at one minute was nine, at five minutes was nine and at ten minutes were not reported. No MCM was identified at birth.  The outcome of the event of 'premature baby 33 to 36 weeks' was not reported.  The reporter did not provide a causality assessment.  The event of 'premature baby 33 to 36 weeks' was considered to be medically significant by a Physician within Seqirus's.  This case is linked to cases 202007471 (the corresponding mother case) and 202101843 (the corresponding baby brother case).  Company comment:The neonate was born as premature baby 5 months and 23 days after foetal exposure to the suspect product, Afluria QIV. Chronology is implausible. The neonate's mother medical history of high body mass index and underlying twin pregnancy confounds causality for the event. Causality between the suspect product and the event premature baby is assessed as not related due to biological and chronological implausibility and presented confounders. Foetal exposure during pregnancy is assessed as not related per company's conventions.; Sender's Comments: The neonate was born as premature baby 5 months and 23 days after foetal exposure to the suspect product, Afluria QIV. Chronology is implausible. The neonate's mother medical history of high body mass index and underlying twin pregnancy confounds causality for the event. Causality between the suspect product and the event premature baby is assessed as not related due to biological and chronological implausibility and presented confounders. Foetal exposure during pregnancy is assessed as not related per company's conventions.

Developed Guillian Barre Syndrome with Miller Fisher variant; Bell's palsy; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable physician (patient). A 65-year-old male patient received the second dose of BNT162B2 (BNT162B2, lot number was not reported), intramuscular, on 08Jan2021 at a single dose for COVID-19 immunisation. He received the vaccine at a school/student health clinic. The patient did not have COVID prior to vaccination. He did not receive any other vaccines 4 weeks prior to receiving BNT162B2. Medical history included hypertension and hypercholesterolemia, both were from unspecified dates and ongoing. Concomitant medications included ramipril (ALTACE) for hypertension, rosuvastatin calcium (CRESTOR) for hypercholesterolemia, acetylsalicylic acid (ASPIRIN), loratadine (LORATIDINE), evolocumab (REPATHA) for hypercholesterolemia. The patient previously received the first dose of BNT162B2 (BNT162B2, lot number was not reported), intramuscular, on 18Dec2020 for COVID-19 immunisation, at the age of 65-year-old. It was reported that patient developed Guillian Barre Syndrome with Miller Fisher variant 10 days (as reported) after receiving the 2nd dose of the COVID vaccine on 18Jan2021. He lost the ability to use his hands/legs. He received 2 g/kg of IVIG over 4 days starting on 21Jan2021. At the time of initial report (02Mar2021), he was recovering in an inpatient rehab center. The patient also experienced Bell's Palsy on 24Jan2021. The patient further reported that all started with a headache on 18Jan2021 and then he began to lose the ability to use his hands and legs. So, he visited the ER (emergency room) on 20Jan2021 and got hospitalized. On 22Jan2021, he was completely unable to walk. On 24Jan2021, he was also diagnosed with Bell's Palsy which was still ongoing at the time of report. The patient stated that he just got out of the inpatient rehab center on 03Mar2021. At the time of follow-up report (04Mar2021), he stated that he feels better but it is not recovered yet. The patient had undergone laboratory tests and procedures on 20Jan2021 which includes: Blood test: normal, Urine test: normal, CR Protein: elevated, Covid19 test: negative, CT (computer tomography) Scan: normal, MRI (magnetic resonance imaging): normal. It was reported that adverse event Guillain Barre Syndrome with Miller Fisher variant required visit to ER. The patient was hospitalized for Guillian Barre Syndrome with Miller Fisher variant from 20Jan2021 to 03Mar2021. The patient received treatment for Guillian Barre Syndrome with Miller Fisher variant, while he did not receive any treatment for Bell's palsy. Outcome of the event Guillian Barre Syndrome with Miller Fisher variant was recovering, while outcome of Bell's Palsy was not recovered.   Information on batch/lot number was requested.; Sender's Comments: Based on the available information, a possible contribution of the drug to the events  Guillian Barre Syndrome with Miller Fisher variant and Bell's palsy cannot be excluded.  The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committees and Investigators, as appropriate.

The feelings lasted all day Monday, all day Tuesday, got concerned yesterday Wednesday 3/17/21.  She called  the CDC and they transferred her to a nurse who told her to go see her doctor.  She called her doctor and she described her reaction and told her that they did not know if it was stroke-like and they told her to go to the hospital.  She went to the hospital yesterday and they did an exam on her and one of the doctors who consulted with his connections with the CDC and decided that they would have to do an MRI on her to make sure it did not cause a stroke.  She did have the MRI which they looked at it and told her that it looked clear and was not a stroke, however, she is to FU with a Neurologist and her PCP.  The only thing that she was given to try was something for allergies, Benadryl to see if that would help with the reaction.  She still has some feelings of numbness in the same areas as listed above.

Patient received dose of Twinrix, previous documentation of Hep A and Hep B had been given two years prior. Allergies verified, contraindication check list completed and vaccination administered at 10:12am. Walked with patient to front of building to make a second appointment and during that time patient fainted, time of incident occurring 10:14am. RN called for assistance, APRN and other medical staff arrived at the site, vital machine hooked up to patient and oxygen administered with NR mask. Patient began to come to right away, assisted with smelling salts, O2 saturation 100%, HR 47 BP did not register on machine. At this time patient able to verbalize where she was and who she was and that she was feeling better. 10:18am manual bp taken with reading of 100/62, patient sat up and was able to eat a cracker and drink some water that was provided to her. 10:20am, Patient was given Benadryl by APRN, and able to get up to sit in a chair, declined an ambulance and was able to call a ride to pick her up. Patient discharged after being monitored at 10:38am

SYMPTOM_TEXT: At approximately 1 hour after the vaccine, I started itching on the top of my feet. A few seconds later I started itching on my back and head followed by my legs. I became red in the areas that were itching but no hives. These were internal itching that wouldn't resolve with topical hydrocortisone cream which I tried immediately. They felt like they were under the skin and itching would not resolve.  I took 2 Benedryl  (Diphenhydramine HCl 25 mg x 2) and after about 45 minutes the itching resolved itself.  I have had this allergic reaction before to other medicines like beta-blockers, pain relievers & muscle relaxers. The following day I had mild itching so I took one Benedryl. I also had muscle aches all over and later the following day a migraine. The muscle aches and migraines resolved themselves the following day. I took Tylenol for migraine but that didn't touch it. The muscle aches and migraine I do not consider an adverse reaction ... it was to be expected according to the information I read.

My chest felt heavy and when I inhaled it felt like someone was squeezing both lobes of my lungs. I got out of bed and went to the bathroom to urinate. I went back to bed and tried to get back to sleep. The discomfort in my chest continued and seemed to get worse. I got back out of bed at about 2:45 AM and went downstairs where I walked around my living room to see if that would help me feel better. I continued to feel severe discomfort in my chest and lungs. I did not otherwise feel bad. I was not congested. I could  still take a deep breath but it hurt to do so.  I took my temperature and I did not have a fever. At about 3:00 AM I woke up my wife and she drove me to the emergency room at Medical Center. On the car ride to the hospital I started to feel much better. By the time I checked into the emergency room most of my discomfort had dissipated and only a very slight feeling of heaviness remained in my chest.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 9/29/2020, 5 days after dual vaccine at routine appt in the clinic and 2 hours PTA to ER, she had acute onset headache that was rapidly progressive over 15 minutes. NO focal deficits on exam in ER. CT scan confirmed "Acute diffuse subarachnoid hemorrhage most prominently noted in the suprasellar cistern extending into the fourth ventricle, sylvian fissures, quadrigeminal plate cistern, and cerebellar pontine angles suggestive of the aneurysmal rupture." There was no evidence for aneurysm. BP was elevated to max of 158/92 in ER.  She was admitted to the hospital from 9/29/20-10/18/20 with consultations from neurosurgery and PM&R. After hospital admission, she developed vasospasm and was treated with 3% saline and nimodipine. She had 6 total catheter angiograms for diagnosis and IA verapamil infusions for vasospasm. On 10/9/2020, she developed large left cerebellar infarct with small foci of infarct throughout bilateral hemispheres due to vasospasm. She developed hyponatremia and was treated for that. She never required surgical intervention. TSH was normal prior to admission (9/12/20 was 1.99) and during hospital was found to be 0.18 and therefore levothyroxine was decreased to 100mcg.  She is overall doing quite well now with ongoing chronic headaches, managed on TCA, and dizziness for which she has seen PT.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Around 11:35 PM on Thursday March 12, my father dropped his dish and drinking glass. Awokened by the noise, we rushed to him and noticed that his speech was slurred and he was not walking well.  His SpO2 was 94 and his heart rate was in the 140's. His blood pressue was elevated. He has suffered a stroke in November 2020 and he was acting like he did on that day. Once he sat down, he could not get himself up. The paramedics and my brother had to help him into the ambulance where they administered oxygen. The paramedics took him to the hospital, where he was admitted to the ICU. An MRI did not reveal any damage to the brain. He was diagnosed with a TIA and discharged from the hospital on Sunday, March 14.  I am not sure if the vaccine had anything to do with this episode, but I thought it should be reported just in case.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The day after my second shot, March 10, I experienced what I felt were normal side effects that a lot of people have experienced.  But starting March 11, I have experienced dizziness, double vision, blurred vision, headaches, eye pain, and nausea. With regards to my eyes, it feels like they are out of sync.   Severity varies on an hour to hour, daily basis.  I have multiple sclerosis but have not had a relapse in almost 11 years. I was concerned about my right eye because my original MS diagnosis was via optic neuritis. I did see an ophthalmologist March 16 but was told there is no new nerve damage or inflammation. I have since been prescribed a steroid pack and I?ve been scheduled for updated MRIs (with and without contrast ) at the end of this month.   I was 100% healthy and lived a normal life before the second shot. The first shot I had zero side effects except for soreness at the  shot site.
LAB_DATA: On March 16 I saw an ophthalmologist regarding my MS eye.  Was concerned there was something going on there because my eyes felt out of sync. But there is no new nerve damage or inflammation. And the muscles around my eye are fine. Both eyes checked out OK. I am scheduled for updated MRIs at the end of this month.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: MODERNA COVID-19 Vaccine EUA  Patient presented to ED on 3/14/21 with new onset of inability to walk. Recalls not feeling well on 3/4/21 after receiving her COVID-19 vaccine (1st dose) on 2/21/21.  She began to experience aching over the anterior thigh on the following day that progressed to involve the posterior lower extremity and forearms by Saturday, 3/6/21.  She also began to experience numbness and tingling in the feet and fingers at that time.  The sensory symptoms persisted over the following days in association with lower extremity weakness that culminated in a fall at home on Thursday, 3/11/21.  She was unable to walk without assistance at the time of her presentation.  Initial examination in the ED revealed borderline antigravity lower extremity strength and absent lower extremity reflexes.  A lumbar puncture performed on 3/14/21 revealed protein � 218.1, glucose � 76, WBC � 8, and RBC 1. She was admitted to the hospital with the diagnosis of Guillain-Barre syndrome and received her initial dose of IVIG that evening. She has noted some interval improvement in lower extremity muscle strength since her admission to the hospital.  The pain that she had been experiencing is less intense, though she is still prone to experience discomfort if she remains in the same position too long.  She is continuing to experience tingling in the feet and fingers.  She is not experiencing any shortness of breath or difficulty with chewing/swallowing.  She is not experiencing any urinary bladder dysfunction.  She is experiencing constipation.
LAB_DATA: Imaging studies performed yesterday revealed the following: MR brain:  Mild chronic microvascular changes slightly progressed when compared to a prior study performed in 2013. Chronic encephalomalacia in the right frontal lobe associated with previous closed head injury. MR cervical spine:  Multilevel cervical spondylosis associated with severe central canal stenosis at C3-4 and moderate-severe central canal stenosis at C4-5 without abnormal cord signal. MR thoracic spine:  Abnormal enhancement of 2 ventral cauda equina nerve roots near the conus and questionable additional ventral nerve root enhancement bilaterally at the T10-T11 levels. MR lumbar spine:  Multilevel degenerative changes without significant central canal stenosis.

Saturday 3/13 - Moderna shot @10am on L arm. Onset of sx @6pm. Fatigue, irritability, mild body aches   Sunday 3/14 - Upon waking Fatigue and severe body aches. Painful to walk, exert, lift a spoon. Required some assistance with activities of daily living. Nausea. Some improvement around 6pm.   Monday 3/15 - Upon waking Decreased fatigue, body aches resolved, nausea resolved. Soreness and fatigue in carpel tunnel area, feeling as though I had held a heavy phone for too long. Adjusted by keeping off phone during the day. Hand/wrist pain increased in the evening. Noted wrist and hand swelling @8pm. After applying ice around 10:30pm pain became suddenly severe with movement. Suspected ice was somehow a mistake and applied heat. Pain became excruciating. Took tylenol XS to sleep.   Tuesday 3/16 - Upon waking Moderate swelling and complete loss of mobility in both hands and wrists. Shooting pain that knocked the breath out of me. Unable to complete any activities of daily living independently (bathing, toileting, eating). Wore carpel tunnel braces all day. Some improvement in range of motion in the evening, able to open and rest hands semi-flat on an angled surface. R hand demonstrating faster improvement than L. Noted mild red bumps present on both wrists (more on L) and mild-moderate shooting pain from L thumb toward inner elbow, more severe in area closer to elbow. Upon rubbing the area close to elbow noted soreness and bumps under skin when applying mild pressure that aren't visible to the eye.   Wednesday 3/17 - Upon waking Red bumps resolved. Some improvement in all areas. L hand improvements mildly lagging behind the R. Able to complete activities of daily living with supportive assistance. Increased range of motion and moderate pain. More improvement @5pm. Regained 90% range of motion, shooting pains were mild-moderate.   Thursday 3/18 - Upon waking I have full range of motion. Mild-moderate pain with certain angled movements and levels of exertion. PCP telehealth appt @9am. Diagnosis: adverse reaction to moderna. Suspicion that there may be some connection with the complex migraine (though there was no numbness or tingling present) and to update my neurologist (you!). Recommendation was to report it and monitor sx. If sx not completely resolved in one week referral to othopedic.
OTHER_MEDS: citalopram 30mg for depression, adderall xr 10mg, adderall 10mg for ADHD, , magnesium for migraine, emgality shot monthly for migraine,  ubrelvy as needed for migraine (taken within 24 hrs prior to vaccine), vitamin d supplement for vitamin
